@Node Description
@TITLE "Description"



	Description :
	
	~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~


	° If you have already experienced a write error on your HD 
	  further to a cold reset or a switchoff, then ShutAll is
	  for you. 

	    
	° Once executed, ShutAll will open its flashy window on the 
          workbench, or on a public screen. 


	° As a starter, it will inform you that @{b}all disk activities
	  have been stopped@{ub}, enabling you to safely reset or switchoff
	  your computer.

	° Now you have to face the ultimate question : shall I 
	  reboot or cancel this critical action ? Choose wisely !


	° An @{b}IFF sample@{ub}, or ANY OTHER FORMAT included in your
	  sound datatypes list can be played.


	° A collection of suitable samples has been included in
	  case of lack of inspiration. Try them, they are fun !

	° ShutAll is a commodity that would enjoy living in your
          WBStartup drawer, under a Dock or a ToolManager Icon.


	° ShutAll does not use the shutdown.library.


	° ShutAll is small but beautifull.




@EndNode

@Node Prerequis
@TITLE "Configuration"



	ShutAll requires :

	~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

	
	° An Amiga working under KickStart 3.0 (V39) or better.

	
	° MUI 3.3 (or better) to tune.
	



@EndNode

@Node Installation
@TITLE "Installation"



	Installation :

	~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~


	° A self-explanatory install script is supplied.

	° ShutAll and its icon can be placed anywhere.

	° ShutAll Preferences as well.

	° The samples and documentation can also be moved.

	° Easy, isn't it ?

	
@EndNode

@Node Reglages
@TITLE "Réglages"



	Tuning :

	~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~


	° SA_Prefs is the configuration program for ShutAll.


	° It's MUI graphic interface allow you build your sample list
	  

	° Use the right border gadgets to edit and modify it.


	° Selection Mode gives you the choice between never play sam-
	  ple (NONE), play a different sample every time (SEQUENTIAL)
	  or choose a sample randomly in the list (RANDOM).

	° The screen type (Worbench ou custom screen) can be set on
	  the second part of the window.

	
@EndNode

@Node Utilisation
@TITLE "Use"



	Use :
	
	~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~


	° ToolTypes list : 


		CX_POPKEY	-> To call ShutAll  if it  is already 
				   resident
				   
		CX_PRIORITY	-> The commodity priority.

		CX_POPUP	-> Yes means  that ShutAll will popup
				   upon call.




	° ToolManager users (or any other similar program) users can
	  define a specific dock or icon for ShutAll.


	° Once executed, ShutAll will display the following message :

		@{b}Terminating all disk activity...@{ub}


	° All your devices will then be inhibited (floopy disks, hard
	  disk and others).
 

	° The following message appears :

		@{b}It's now safe to reset or switch off...@{ub}


	° If have you decided to switch off your computer,it's really 
	  safe : all disk activities have been stopped.

	
	° The  Cancel  button  enables  you  to  start over  the disk
	  activity where it was stopped. You will return to Workbench
	  and  Shutall  will be hidden.  It is still Alive ! (through
	  its Hotkey).


	° The Reboot button enables you to reboot your computer. This
	  is especially  usefull for Amiga 1200  tower  users who can
	  not reset their computer using the keyboard.


	° A small animation and a sample precede the rebooting.


	° ShutAll can also be run from Shell.



@EndNode

